description:
&lt;p&gt;North Staffordshire Combined Healthcare NHS Trust has an ‘Outstanding’ CQC rating and is focussed on continuous improvement. The Trust has recently published an ambitious strategy to support implementation of the NHS Long Term Plan and is strengthening our Programme Management Office to provide more support to Project Managers across our organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an important role that will be vital in our desire to enhance our programme management capability as we enter an exciting period of clinical and corporate transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working to the Business Development Manager, the role focusses on running the PMO to ensure accurate reporting and monitoring of our project portfolio to enable clear visibility on progress to our Senior Leadership Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also require you to add value to the PMO offer to our Project Managers through the provision of advice, guidance and training to promote a skills-based approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need a strong grasp of PMO principles and be able to deploy them in a way that reflects the culture and values of the Trust. This will require strong interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate effectively with Project Managers and other stakeholders is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Karen Day - &lt;/em&gt;Mobile 07725639732 or karen.day@combined.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
